BT 1 0 0 1 0 110 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL 1.487893 Tw (Of course, not all classes lend themselves to writing on the board. For instance, when I taught Computer) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.464945 Tw (Graphics, I used a mixture of board-based lectures and slide presentations since some of the material) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.580261 Tw (required a richer medium. In these cases, other tactics for engaging the students are required. One such) Tj T* 0 Tw .114951 Tw (method I have utilized is to have students answer review questions during class. This compels the students to) Tj T* 0 Tw .478565 Tw (be current with the material and provides a good basis for discussion. Another method I have employed is to) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.075298 Tw (have students present their solutions to assignments. This can often lead to interesting debates over) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.641012 Tw (programming techniques and strategy, especially if you allow other students to review the solutions. A) Tj T* 0 Tw .263209 Tw (technique I have not yet tried, but plan on using in the future, is to have students brainstorm answers in small) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.156343 Tw (groups and then have a representative report back to the whole class. All of these methods help foster an) Tj T* 0 Tw (open and participatory learning environment, which in turn keeps the students focused and engaged.) Tj T* ET
