BT 1 0 0 1 0 98 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL 1.685298 Tw (Having fun and innovative assignments is another effective means of engaging students. In fact, creating) Tj T* 0 Tw .205612 Tw (programming assignments is my favorite part of teaching. When I assisted in the Fundamentals of Computing) Tj T* 0 Tw .299676 Tw (course, I designed a lab that required using a graphical toolkit to program a "battleship" game. Having such a) Tj T* 0 Tw 1.486716 Tw (fun goal for a lab motivated the students to tackle the topic of graphical user interfaces, something which) Tj T* 0 Tw 3.44109 Tw (previous classes struggled to understand. In the teacher evaluations for the Computer Graphics and) Tj T* 0 Tw .834016 Tw (Programming Challenges courses, students frequently complimented the assignments I designed and noted) Tj T* 0 Tw .736716 Tw (how useful they were in helping the students master the concepts covered in class. From my experience as) Tj T* 0 Tw .079069 Tw (both a student and an instructor, I have found that well-designed assignments not only help students learn the) Tj T* 0 Tw (material, but also work in keeping students interested and motivated.) Tj T* ET
