BT 1 0 0 1 0 98 Tm /F1 10 Tf 12 TL .685612 Tw (Good programming assignments also help in another essential part of teaching, which is to promote student) Tj T* 0 Tw .485709 Tw (creativity. Personally, I have found that I learn best by doing. The beauty of Computer Science is that it is so) Tj T* 0 Tw .067709 Tw (easy \(and fun\) to explore and play around with the ideas you learn about; you just need a computer and some) Tj T* 0 Tw 2.374936 Tw (inspiration. When creating programming assignments, I try to ensure that each assignment reinforces a) Tj T* 0 Tw .109121 Tw (specific concept I am trying to teach, while still allowing the students to explore. For instance, in the Computer) Tj T* 0 Tw .399011 Tw (Graphics course, I often created assignments that required specific methods to be utilized, but left the details) Tj T* 0 Tw .632454 Tw (of the graphics to the students. So in an assignment involving modeling a vehicle, students came up with all) Tj T* 0 Tw .181422 Tw (sorts of entertaining programs with objects such as UFOs, rockets, and even a bear riding a scooter. Allowing) Tj T* 0 Tw (the students to personalize their solutions enabled them to develop a deeper understanding of the material.) Tj T* ET
